  (text " RN2483 breakout Module\n" 
    (exclude_from_sim no) 
    (at 73.406 133.604 0) 
    (effects 
      (font 
        (size 1.27 1.27))) 
    (uuid "ede21f82-0137-4ac6-b237-51491754c481")) 
  (text_box "Design Choices - Water Leakage Sensor\nDate: 06/04/2026\n\n-Resistive water leakage sensor connected via 3-pin 2.54mm socket connector (J_WATER) on PCB - VCC, GND, DO (digital output).\n\n-Digital output used over analog - for leakage detection a simple HIGH/LOW flood detection is sufficient, no need for water level readings.\n\n-DO connected to ESP32 GPIO33 (ADC1_CH5) via net label WATER_LEAK. ADC1 chosen - reliable when LoRa radio is active.\n\n-Physical placement: sensor connected via cable to the connector on PCB. Sensor itself embedded inside the 3D printed enclosure, lying flat at the bottom/side to detect any water pooling inside the case from rain, irrigation splash, or condensation. Cable length should be kept short.\n" 
    (exclude_from_sim no) 
    (at 182.88 115.57 0) 
    (size 25.4 16.5099) 
    (margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525) 
    (stroke 
      (width 0) 
      (type solid)) 
    (fill 
      (type none)) 
    (effects 
      (font 
        (face "Arial") 
        (size 0.508 0.508)) 
      (justify left top)) 
    (uuid "058eec81-6354-4162-8f15-f7c34fa54e98")) 
  (text_box "Date: Design Choices - Soil Moisture\nDate: 07/04/2026\n\n-Capacitive Soil Moisture Sensor v1.2 selected over resistive type — capacitive does not corrode over time, significantly more reliable for permanent greenhouse deployment where sensor stays in soil continuously.\n\n-JST PH 2.0mm 3-pin connector (J_SOIL) used to match the sensor's onboard cable — VCC, GND, AOUT. Note: this is 2.0mm pitch, not standard 2.54mm — verify footprint before PCB manufacture.\n\n-AOUT connected to ESP32 GPIO32 (ADC1_CH4) via net label SOIL_MOIST. ADC1 chosen deliberately — remains reliable when LoRa radio is active, unlike ADC2 pins.\n\n-Mechanical note: the sensor probe can double as a structural anchor into the soil, fixing the sensor node physically in the greenhouse bed. Consider mounting angle and cable strain relief in enclosure design.\n\n-Future improvement: a low-pass RC filter on the AOUT line (e.g. 10kΩ + 100nF) should be considered to reduce high-frequency noise, up for discurssion." 
    (exclude_from_sim no) 
    (at 182.88 92.71 0) 
    (size 25.4 21.4766) 
    (margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525) 
    (stroke 
      (width 0) 
      (type solid)) 
    (fill 
      (type none)) 
    (effects 
      (font 
        (face "Arial") 
        (size 0.508 0.508)) 
      (justify left top)) 
    (uuid "3f799e43-b96a-4f24-916a-9a210e7cdb44")) 
  (text_box "" 
    (exclude_from_sim no) 
    (at 69.85 52.07 0) 
    (size 0 0) 
    (margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525) 
    (stroke 
      (width 0) 
      (type solid)) 
    (fill 
      (type none)) 
    (effects 
      (font 
        (size 0.254 0.254)) 
      (justify left top)) 
    (uuid "4f1460b0-c66f-45e2-91d0-b4cd89c6e796")) 
  (text_box "Design Choices - LoRa Module (RN2483 DrAzzy Breakout Rev.C)\nDate: 06/04/2026\n\n-RN2483A Microchip LoRa module on DrAzzy breakout board Rev.C, communicates via UART (not SPI) at 57600 baud.\n\n-Two 2.54mm female socket connectors on PCB - J2 (7-pin serial/power) and J3 (14-pin GPIO). Both needed for mechanical stability so module pins pass through PCB on both sides. Only J2 carries functional signals.\n" 
    (exclude_from_sim no) 
    (at 60.96 154.9401 0) 
    (size 53.34 11.4299) 
    (margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525) 
    (stroke 
      (width 0) 
      (type solid)) 
    (fill 
      (type none)) 
    (effects 
      (font 
        (face "Arial") 
        (size 0.508 0.508)) 
      (justify left top)) 
    (uuid "72de7b6c-551c-4467-abd3-0e0ab5ebcfa2")) 
  (text_box "Design Choices - Temperature and Humidity Sensor\nDate: 03/04/2026\n\n-DHT22 (AM2302) selected over DHT11 for higher accuracy (±0.5°C vs ±2°C) and wider temperature range (-40°C to +80°C), better suited for greenhouse monitoring.\n\n-Same footprint as DHT11 (pin-for-pin compatible) - can be swapped back to DHT11 if needed without PCB changes.\n\n-DATA line (pin 2) connected to ESP32 GPIO4 via net label TH.\n\n-R2 4.7kΩ pull-up resistor on DATA line to +3V3 - datasheet recomend\n\n-C5 100nF ceramic decoupling capacitor between VDD and GND, placed close to sensor - filters power supply noise( Not sure how much is needed)\n\nPowered directly from +3V3 rail - compatible with 3.3V logic, no level shifting needed to ESP32." 
    (exclude_from_sim no) 
    (at 194.31 59.69 0) 
    (size 13.97 31.7499) 
    (margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525) 
    (stroke 
      (width 0) 
      (type solid)) 
    (fill 
      (type none)) 
    (effects 
      (font 
        (face "Arial") 
        (size 0.508 0.508)) 
      (justify left top)) 
    (uuid "82b10290-64c4-4999-a759-86454895b9cc")) 
  (text_box "Design Choices - Power Management\nDate: 03/04/2026\n\n-AO3401A P-channel MOSFET (SOT-23-5 HandSoldering footprint) for reverse polarity protection on battery input. Source faces battery+, Drain faces LDO VIN. Gate pulled to GND via 10kΩ resistor (R1) for ESD protection. MOSFET turns ON when Vgs goes negative (normal polarity).\n\n-AP2112K-3.3 LDO (SOT-23-5 HandSoldering footprint) regulates battery voltage (~3.7-4.2V LiPo) down to 3.3V. Rated 600mA max - sufficient for ESP32 + LoRa + sensors (~300-350mA worst case). Dropout voltage ~300mV at full load, meaning LDO requires minimum ~3.6V input - monitor battery sag on low charge.\n\n-LDO EN (pin 3) tied to VIN (pin 1) - LDO is always enabled. Simpler design but no firmware power-gating possible. Increases idle battery consumption.\n\n-Ceramic unpolarized capacitors (C2 10µF, C1 10µF) placed close to LDO on input and output for high-frequency noise filtering.\n\n-Polarized electrolytic capacitors (C3 100µF input, C4 100µF output) for bulk charge storage and transient current support during ESP32/LoRa TX bursts." 
    (exclude_from_sim no) 
    (at 59.69 43.18 0) 
    (size 22.86 24.1299) 
    (margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525) 
    (stroke 
      (width 0) 
      (type solid)) 
    (fill 
      (type none)) 
    (effects 
      (font 
        (face "Arial") 
        (size 0.508 0.508)) 
      (justify left top)) 
    (uuid "8357a042-1e95-42ab-86aa-430b328057dd")) 
  (text_box "Design Choices - Light Intensity Sensor (BH1750)\nDate: 06/04/2026\n\n-BH1750 selected for I2C interface, real lux measurements suitable for plant growth monitoring, and non-conflicting I2C address (0x23) alongside OLED (0x3C).\n\n-4-pin 2.54mm socket connector (J_LIGHT) on PCB - VCC, GND, SDA, SCL. Sensor connected via cable running outside the 3D printed enclosure, mounted facing upward for accurate ambient light readings.\n\n-I2C_SDA and I2C_SCL net labels shared with OLED display on GPIO21 and GPIO22.\n\n-Cable length should be kept under 30cm for reliable I2C communication. If longer cable required in future, consider stronger pullup resistors (2.2kΩ instead of 4.7kΩ).\n" 
    (exclude_from_sim no) 
    (at 184.15 133.35 0) 
    (size 24.13 17.78) 
    (margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525) 
    (stroke 
      (width 0) 
      (type solid)) 
    (fill 
      (type none)) 
    (effects 
      (font 
        (face "Arial") 
        (size 0.508 0.508)) 
      (justify left top)) 
    (uuid "ae2e2bf8-33eb-4f1a-8d71-a59e9964aa24")) 
